{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH82YEJ4Xa3HPJg8YB9j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**The bug** (`src/userService.js:10`): the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it left out `includeArchived`. When one request loaded a team *with* archived users, that result got cached under the team-only key, and the next request for the same team *without* archived users hit the same key and got the archived list back. The 60s TTL is why refreshing after a minute clears it.\n\n**The fix:** include `includeArchived` in the cache key so the two variants get separate entries:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"archived\" : \"active\"}`;\n```\n\nNote: the existing test suite (`test/cache.test.js`) only covers the cache primitive, not `getUsers`, so it doesn't exercise this path directly. Want me to add a regression test for the key collision in `userService`?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":298,"cache_read_input_tokens":23763,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":298},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0990abe5-0b0b-451b-8d69-62d6ff8b2c20","uuid":"3c09d8e8-ada1-4490-a6ff-6b4aef739456","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:48:13.990Z","request_id":"req_011CdH82W2qWBqs7HXbjMbVf"}
